review_blob: On tap in tasting room. Pours clear golden color with a white head. Aroma of biscuits and floral hops. Taste of biscuity malt profile and floral and grassy hops.

On tap in tasting room. Pour crystal clear golden with a thin white head. Aroma of Noble hops and biscuity pilsner malt. Flavor is crisp and clean with the Noble hops shining and a biscuity malt character in the background.
On tap in tap room. Pours hazy golden with a thick white head. Aroma of pear and lemon zest. Tastes is fantastic with a lemon citrus hop finish on the beer and a full body feel.
On Tap in Tap room. Pours clear brown with a tan head that sticks around and leaves nice lacing. Aroma full of nutty chocolate and roasted barley. Medium body.
Up front caramel nose balanced with a great northwestern hop profile (piney with a hint of citrus). Body is medium and pours with a nice white head and crystal clear amber color.
